Go, well parting in&H4; a morning is past remedy at midnight, God be with ye sir, I could weep, but my tears will&H1; not pleasure ye, 
         if I see ye no&H2; more till I see ye again, god have ye in&H4; his kitchen. As for&H4; you two I shall see you lest in&H4; pledge till I have drunk to&H4; you, 
         and you pledged me twenty times: once more adiew.

Sanctiamen, God give me joy and luck in&H4; mine office. 
                              Now boys beware that&H3; ye wipe not your noses on&H4; your sleeves, 
         for&H3; if ye do, off goes your arm with the Church door key. And dogs keep out of the Chancel, 
         ye shall smell of the whip else. And honest Prentices, if ye please me, I will&H1; 
                              not ring the four o'clock Bell till it be past five: 
         an occupation and an office? now I see I shall thrive.
